# Screen contract (spec adherence)

`screen_contract.json` in `.agent/features/<feature>/` is the machine-readable **ТЗ** for one screen. It exists so that "did we build what was asked" is a **checkable gate**, not a feeling.

| Phase | Obligation |
|-------|-----------|
| **layout** | Create/update the contract from user ТЗ + design. No contract → layout is not done |
| **plan** | `contract_coverage[]` — every acceptance and interaction item covered or omitted with reason |
| **build** | Implement covered items; stubs stay stubs (`level: stub`) |
| **inspect** | `contract_checks[]` — verdict per `verify_by: inspect` item |
| **debug/fix** | A failed contract check is a queue item like any visual gap |

## Shape

```json
{
  "version": 1,
  "feature": "<slug>",
  "source": "user ТЗ | design-derived | mixed",
  "jtbd": "Когда я …, я хочу …, чтобы …",
  "acceptance": [
    { "id": "A1", "statement": "Футер с CTA прижат к низу и не скроллится", "verify_by": "inspect" }
  ],
  "interactions": [
    { "id": "I1", "figma_ids": ["…"], "expect": "Тап по CTA — переход к оплате (stub)", "level": "stub" }
  ],
  "states": [
    { "id": "S1", "name": "loading", "in_scope": false }
  ],
  "out_of_scope": [],
  "open_questions": []
}
```

- `verify_by`: `inspect` (visual/PNG) | `analyze` (compiles, lint) | `user` (only the user can confirm)
- `level`: `stub` (handler exists, no logic) | `wired` (logic requested by user)
- Prose values — Russian (`reports-locale.mdc`); ids `A*` / `I*` / `S*` stable across re-runs.

## Rules

- **No user ТЗ given** → derive the contract from the design itself: every `interactive: yes` node becomes an `I*`; baseline acceptance = "screen matches figma.png with no P0/P1 gaps". Mark `source: design-derived`.
- User words are **quoted, not paraphrased** into new requirements. Inventing scope = drift.
- Contract changes mid-flow (user adds ТЗ) → update the contract first, then re-enter **plan**. Never patch `lib/` against an unwritten requirement.
- `out_of_scope` is explicit — silence is not an omission record.
- Verified mechanically: `node .agent/tools/check.mjs --phase contract` (shape) and `--phase plan` / `--phase inspect` (coverage / checks).
